main event: Three unidentified objects were sighted in the sky near Snowmass, Colorado on December 18, 1963.
interesting points: The objects were observed from sunset until it was completely dark, for at least an hour.
One of the objects was described as being black and red in color when viewed through binoculars.
The objects were seen moving slowly, standing still, and then moving again.
Two of the objects did not appear to move much, with one being partially obscured by clouds.
A neighbor who lived about 5 miles away also reported seeing several of these objects.
witnesses: a local resident and their neighbor
photographs: no photographs included in the report
